Cincinnati Business Courier





In This Article






Retailing






 


 















 Enlarge





                ​Kroger Co. issued a customer warning and a recall of two separate products this week.            

                Daniel Acker | Bloomberg            






Kroger Co. issued a customer warning and a recall of two separate products this week.
The Cincinnati-based grocer (NYSE: KR) has issued a recall of its Simple Truth Dry Roasted Macadamia Nuts due to a potential listeria contamination along with a warning that its Yellow Sponge Cake Dessert Cups contain an allergen that isn’t listed on the package.











 Enlarge





                ​Kroger Co. issued a customer warning and a recall of two separate products this week.            
Daniel Acker | Bloomberg






 


The recalled Macadamia nuts come in 12-ounce clear plastic packages and have an expiration date of May 2, 2018. The products have been removed from Kroger shelves and customers who may have purchased them could receive messages on their receipts along with phone calls.
The dessert cups don’t pose a health risk except to anyone with an allergy or sensitivity to milk. Milk was listed as an ingredient on the packages but not in the “Contains” statement about allergens. The affected products were sold at a variety of Kroger banner name stores and come in packs of six.
Customers who have purchased either product should not consume them and return them to a store for refund or replacement.
Kroger has 2,796 retail food stores under a variety of local banner names in 35 states and the District of Columbia that employ 443,000 associates.








 




